{
  "id": "019d34e5-0493-7711-9da3-cec7c1ffdbdd",
  "content": "# Spoke Dashboard Integration (Phase 2) -- Decision Record (2026-03-28)\n\n## What: Added spoke container visibility to the existing dashboard AgentsView via GET /api/dashboard/spokes endpoint and frontend enrichment.\n\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. Raw Docker Unix socket HTTP instead of bollard crate in corvia-server. Bollard pulls axum 0.7 which breaks all axum 0.8 handler trait bounds when any bollard type appears in the compilation unit. Even type-erased (dyn Any) or tokio::spawn-isolated approaches failed. The only working solution: query Docker directly via HTTP/1.0 over Unix socket with serde deserialization.\n2. Removed spoke_count/spokes_running from DashboardStatusResponse. Adding any async call to status_handler pushes its future past axum 0.8's handler trait bound limit (dual axum issue). Frontend computes counts client-side from the dedicated /spokes endpoint.\n3. docker_available flag (bool) in AppState instead of cached Docker client. Startup-time check, actual queries created on-demand in tokio::spawn tasks.\n4. SpokeInfo extended with created, health, repo_url fields in corvia-kernel for dashboard consumption.\n\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering:\n- The corvia.repo_url Docker label was missing from SpokeProvisioner::create(). Without it, issue links in the dashboard are always dead links (#).\n- Any reference to corvia_kernel::spoke types from corvia-server (even in separate submodules, even via dyn Any) causes the dual-axum handler trait bound failure. The ONLY safe approach: zero bollard/spoke imports in corvia-server, query Docker directly.\n- status_handler is already at the complexity limit for axum 0.8 Handler trait. Adding ANY additional .await call to it (even tokio::spawn) breaks compilation.\n\n## What Blocked / Surprised:\n- Dual axum 0.7/0.8 was far more aggressive than expected. Not just handler futures, but ANY type transitively containing bollard types in the same crate breaks ALL handlers. Required 4 iterations to find a working approach (direct bollard -> type-erased dyn Any -> SpokeProvisioner in AppState -> raw Unix socket).",
  "source_version": "mcp",
